@host = http://localhost:5160

### 1. Log in as the seeded admin. Returns a REAL JWT in accessToken.
# Paste the accessToken at jwt.io - it decodes, and the payload contains "role": "Admin".
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### 2. Wrong password. 401 Unauthorized (lockout applies after repeated failures).
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "wrong"
}

### 3. Call the protected endpoint WITHOUT a token. 401 Unauthorized.
GET {{host}}/api/products

### 4. Call the protected endpoint WITH the JWT. 200 OK.
@token = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
GET {{host}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
